cs.CL, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.SD, cs.HC 

This paper involves natural language processing techniques for converting spoken English language queries into SQL queries for retrieving data from a relational database management system. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves database management systems, which suggests the category cs.DB (Databases). Additionally, the paper uses rule-based translation and syntax-directed translation techniques, which are related to artificial intelligence and programming languages, respectively, suggesting the categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SD (Software Development). Finally, the paper involves user interfaces for speech input, which suggests the category cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
